abstract: It was a mostly bloodless evening among the 10 candidates onstage, but there were some standout moments.
snippet: It was a mostly bloodless evening among the 10 candidates onstage, but there were some standout moments.
lead_paragraph: With polls showing a highly competitive primary race and no clear front-runner, the Democrats in Wednesdayâ€™s debate acted as if they had decided ahead of time to avoid taking risks or doing much of anything that might cause them to lose momentum at this stage of the campaign.

abstract: Mr. Messam, the mayor of Miramar, Fla., was trying to do what nobody has ever done: get elected president straight from a mayorship. But his campaign barely registered.

lead_paragraph: Wayne Messam, the mayor of Miramar, Fla., has ended a presidential campaign that barely got off the ground.

abstract: Joseph R. Biden Jr. has durable support from a multiracial coalition of working-class voters who view him as one of their own.
snippet: Joseph R. Biden Jr. has durable support from a multiracial coalition of working-class voters who view him as one of their own.
lead_paragraph: WEST POINT, Iowa â€” They are white and nonwhite alike, prefer Facebook over Twitter, if they are on social media at all, and can be hard to find at Democratic campaign events dominated by activists from the professional class. But these blue-collar voters could go a long way toward determining who captures the Democratic presidential nomination â€” and Joseph R. Biden Jr. is racing to press his advantage with that constituency.
